5:
Night approaches. 
Can you pick up the pace, Alk?
9:
I'm trying! The ground is REALLY 
uneven, okay?
12:
All the more reason to hurry home 
while there's light. It also makes us 
more vulnerable to attac—
20: Sorry, friend. I'm over here! Look up.
25:
I shouldn't hunt when I'm sleepy, eh? 
That was a close call.
30:
Hunt? Wait.
Were you TRYING to hit me?!
34:
I'm afraid I was. You looked the perfect 
size for dinner, but... if you can talk, 
you don't belong on a plate, do you?
36:
I'm Aurore. Birdfolk. It's nice to meet 
you both, er...
40:
Alk. I'm Alk, and this is Light. He looks 
small now, but he's actually the 
champion!
45:
Champion? Well. I'm terribly sorry to 
have pointed a weapon at you, 
Champion Light. I hope you don't 
mind too much.
48:
I'd best save the hunt for another day, 
eh? I'll take a little stroll, clear my head 
a bit.  'Til another time, friends. 
Farewell!
53:
...And he's gone.
Are you okay, Light?
58:
I almost died, and yet he...
Ju- just who WAS that man?!
61:
I wonder...
He was birdfolk, right? It's amazing 
how they can fly like that.
66: Look, Alk! That must be him.
70: Wow, he's already flown so high!
74:
Why's he zig-zagging all over the 
place though? Is that what he meant 
by going for a stroll?
78:
No, something isn't right. Look, he's 
losing altitude!
84:
Huh? W-whoa, you're right!
He's falling! Light, what should we do?!
94:
Thank goodness, he's still—
Wait, is he... snoring?
100:
Champion Light, Alk, thank you for the 
aid.
The winds brought us together again, 
eh?
105:
How can you be so calm?! 
More importantly, how did you fall 
asleep while FLYING?! Isn't that 
dangerous?!
108:
Well, there was a nice evening breeze. 
Right above the cloudline, strong 
enough to cruise.
110:
Warm sunlight, cool clouds. Me, 
floating along, letting the current carry 
me...
When I opened my eyes, here I was.
113:
I spent last night stargazing. Before 
I knew it, the sun rose.
I guess the lack of sleep caught up 
with me.
118:
*sigh*
Stretch out your arms and legs. 
Does anything hurt? Feel broken?
125:
That's odd... 
I sleep and fly all the time, but I've 
never gotten hurt.
128:
Everyone makes mistakes. Please, DO 
be more careful though.
131:
I will. Gliding is not flying, and what 
does not fly, falls.
134:
Is that a birdfolk saying? It has a nice 
ring to it.
138:
A saying?
No, just a musing of mine.
142:
What wise words from someone who 
decided to take a nap leagues up in 
the air...
I would love to know WHAT goes 
through your head.
150:
What are we to do with him, Alk? We 
can't leave him with these injuries, but 
he DID try to put a halberd through 
me.
154:
Only because he mistook you for an 
animal. He definitely doesn't seem like 
a bad guy. Let's take him back with us.
159:
Very well. Aurore, we can treat your 
wounds.
Can we trust you to keep the location 
of our base secret? It's... An unusual 
place.
164:
Of course. That's the least I could do. 
And I love to explore new places!
169:
Where are we? ...What are those?!
I've never seen stars so big!
172:
They do look like stars, but they're 
actually worlds! We've been to a few of 
them, like your home world.
180:
You mean you can visit them? You 
HAVE visited them? But... how do you 
reach the stars without wings?
184:
Um, that's a good question. I guess the 
World Flipper just... flips us over?
188:
Amazing. To think, the winds would 
guide me to star-hoppers.
191:
I can't say no to a chance like this, eh? 
If I stay here, then I'll... I'll finally reach 
them—the stars...
